        "desc": "The eastern wall of this small, quiet home is decorated as part of a tree's\ntrunk, crooked and bark-like. The backrest of the cushiony sofa standing nearby\nmatches well, replicating the crook of a tree's trunk. In the centre of the room\nstands a round three-legged table, covered with a green spread woven from sweet\nsmelling leaves. On the table has been placed a crystal vase filled with fruit.\nOn the southern wall there is a bookshelf filled with books. At first glance,\nsome of the books look plain, but with a skilled eye one recognizes the fine\nwork of a true master.\n",
